  > Does zsh "natively" support fetching history entries from multiple files?
  
  Yes. You can load anything into active history with `fc -RI`.
  
  > If so, how does sorting/matching work with fzf?
  
  You can define any matching you like. I do it like this: first match history from my current machine, then from other machines. You can even create multiple modes: strictly by timestamp across all machines; my machine first then by timestamps, etc.
  
